(got info about database connection)
can save report in different formats.
#Dirb
takes wordlists and requests them from target 
web app & returns HTTP response code.

cd /usr/share/dirb/wordlists

`dirb http://google.com /usr/share/dirb/worlists/small.txt`

Custom wordlists avails on github

dirb -a (user agent string) http://useragentstring.com/pages/useragentstring.php
ex:
`dirb http://google.com -a "Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.0.8) Gecko/20090327 Galeon/2.0.7"

dirb -p to specify a proxy.
ex:
`dirb http:// 192.168.0.33 -p http://127.0.0.1:8080 -c "COOKIE:XYZ"`
(integration with burp.)

dirb <target site> -p http://127.0.0.1:8080 -u "admin:password"
#can use burp decoder to decode the passed traffic)
dirb <target site> -p http://127.0.0.1:8080 -H "MyHeader:My Content"
#slow down requests with -z flag for firewall evasion
dirb <target site> -z 1000 (1 request / sec)
